<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1957-12-23T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-01-06T10:00:00-05:00" n="276" subtype="editorial-note" type="document" xml:id="d276">
                            <head>276. Editorial Note</head>
                            <p>Between 4:04 and 4:24 p.m. on March 22, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1">Eisenhower</persName>, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1">Dulles</persName>, and General <persName corresp="#p_GCAJ1">Goodpaster</persName> met with Prime Minister
                                    <persName corresp="#p_MH1">Macmillan</persName>, Foreign
                                Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LSJSB1">Lloyd</persName>, and
                                    <persName corresp="#p_DPH1">Patrick Dean</persName>. (Eisenhower
                                Library, President’s Appointment Book) No record of this
                                conversation has been found in Department of State files.</p>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>